# Service Policy
#
# Optional per-user config for the service reload /
# restart policy. See `rules/service-reload.md` for
# the full policy. Missing file = defaults apply
# (reload auto-proceeds, restart asks).
#
# Format: one service name per line under each
# section heading. Lines starting with `#` and blank
# lines are ignored. Match by systemd unit name
# without `.service` — e.g. `postgresql`, not
# `postgresql.service`. For templated units, use
# the full instance name (e.g. `nginx@default`).

## reload-always-ask
# Services listed here will NOT auto-reload —
# heinzel will ask before every `systemctl reload`.
# Use for stateful services where a bad config
# reload could cause real damage.
#
# - postgresql
# - mariadb

## restart-auto
# Services listed here WILL auto-restart —
# heinzel will run `systemctl restart` without
# asking. Use for services that come back up
# quickly and are not critical (e.g. reverse
# proxies, stateless workers).
#
# - nginx
# - caddy
# - unbound

## restart-never
# Services listed here CANNOT be restarted by
# heinzel automatically — heinzel will refuse the
# restart outright, without prompting, and tell
# you to do it manually (or remove the entry).
# Use for databases and anything where you want
# to control every restart yourself.
#
# - postgresql
# - mariadb
